  doi = {10.3389/fpsyg.2017.02061},
  note = {
  CORE ARGUMENT: Defends extended mind against Adams & Aizawa's two main
  criticisms by arguing (1) their proposed mark of the cognitive (non-derived
  content) fails to secure intracranialism because neural content is often
  derived, and (2) the coupling-constitution fallacy charge misunderstands
